# SindriStudio — Cline Autonomous Development Rules
# Version: 2.1 — Forge Edition
# Governs ALL Cline sessions across SindriStudio, AnvilML, and BloomeryUI.
# Read this file COMPLETELY before taking any action in any session.
# This file is placed in the SindriStudio root repo and applies to all submodule sessions.

# ━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━
# PRIME DIRECTIVE
# ━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━
#
# ONE TASK PER SESSION. Every session executes exactly this cycle:
#
#   STEP 1 — PLAN       Read spec. Write plan to report. No code yet. STOP.
#   STEP 2 — IMPLEMENT  Write exactly what the plan defines. Tests included.
#   STEP 3 — TEST       Run all tests. All must pass. Record results.
#   STEP 4 — COMMIT     Commit + push. Finalize report. Call new_task. STOP.
#
# When step 4 is complete, call new_task and STOP. Do nothing else.
# Never combine two tasks into one session, even if the second seems trivial.
# Never start step 2 until the plan is complete (report plan section written).
# ━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━

## PRODUCT IDENTITY
- Product:            SindriStudio
- Launcher binary:    sindristudio / sindristudio.exe
- Backend submodule:  AnvilML    → backend/   (https://github.com/DrywFiltiarn/AnvilML.git)
- Frontend submodule: BloomeryUI → frontend/  (https://github.com/DrywFiltiarn/BloomeryUI.git)
- Root repo:          https://github.com/DrywFiltiarn/SindriStudio.git
- Active branch:      develop
- Production branch:  main

## FORGE ORCHESTRATION — HOW THIS SESSION WAS STARTED
# This session was launched by forge.py, the Forge Orchestrator.
# The Forge is running as a long-lived Python process outside this session.
# Your job is to complete the task injected into this session's prompt.
# When STEP 4 is complete, call new_task — the Forge will handle what happens next.
# Do not attempt to communicate with the Forge or read forge/ directory files.

## SESSION INITIALIZATION — EXECUTE IN ORDER BEFORE TOUCHING ANY FILE

1. Read `.cline/state/CURRENT_TASK.md`
   - Does not exist → fresh start. Read docs/TASKS_PHASE1.md, begin task P1-A1.
   - Exists → read completely. This defines what you are doing right now.

2. Read the previous task report if it exists:
   `.cline/reports/{previous-task-id}.md`
   - Verify every file listed under "Files Created" actually exists on disk.
   - If any claimed file is missing: STOP. Report to user. Do not proceed.
   - If all files verified: continue.

3. Read relevant docs (always read ENVIRONMENT.md and ARCHITECTURE.md):
   - docs/ENVIRONMENT.md          — always
   - docs/ARCHITECTURE.md         — always
   - docs/API_CONTRACT.md         — any task touching API, server, or frontend
   - docs/IPC_PROTOCOL.md         — any task touching worker, scheduler, or IPC
   - docs/TESTING_STRATEGY.md     — any task writing tests
   - docs/TASKS_PHASE{N}.md       — the current phase task list

4. Verify prerequisites for the current task (listed in each task spec).
   If a prerequisite is not met: STOP and report to user.

## STEP 1 — PLAN (no code)

- Read the task spec fully from docs/TASKS_PHASE{N}.md.
- Create `.cline/reports/{TASK-ID}.md` and write the Plan section:
  - Every file to be created or modified with purpose
  - How correctness will be verified
  - Any decisions made that are not in the spec
- Update CURRENT_TASK.md: Step = 1-PLAN, Status = COMPLETE
- Do NOT write any application or test code during this step.
- After writing the report plan section and updating CURRENT_TASK.md: STOP.
  The Forge will read the plan and request approval before proceeding.
  When this session resumes with the approved plan, begin STEP 2.

## STEP 2 — IMPLEMENT (code + tests together)

- Implement only what is in the plan. Scope is fixed at step 1.
- If you find yourself creating a file not in the plan:
  STOP. Does it belong to this task? If yes, update plan section of report first.
  If no, note it as a future task and do not create it.
- Write application code AND test code in this step. Tests are not a separate step.
- After all files written: run the build.
  - Backend: `cargo build` from backend/
  - Frontend: `pnpm build` from frontend/
  - Build must succeed before moving to step 3. Fix failures now.
- Update CURRENT_TASK.md: Step = 2-IMPLEMENT, list all created/modified files.

## STEP 3 — TEST (all tests must pass)

Run tests for the affected scope:

  Backend (one crate changed):    cargo test -p {crate-name} -- --nocapture
  Backend (multiple crates):      cargo test -- --nocapture
  Frontend:                       pnpm test --run (from frontend/)
  Python worker:                  ANVILML_WORKER_MOCK=1 python -m pytest backend/worker/tests/ -v

Rules:
- ALL tests must pass. Zero failing tests at commit time.
- Do not comment out, skip, or mark tests as ignored to force a pass.
- If tests fail: fix the code (return to step 2 logic). Re-run tests.
  Repeat until passing. This is normal — stay in the session.
- Capture the complete test output.
- Write test results to the report (commands run, exit codes, pass/fail counts).
- Update CURRENT_TASK.md: Step = 3-TEST, record results.

## STEP 4 — COMMIT (commit + push + report + new_task)

Execute commits in this exact order. Only commit repos that were modified.

```bash
# Backend (if modified)
cd backend
git add -A
git commit -m "feat(scope): description

Task: {TASK-ID}
Tests: {N} passed, 0 failed"
git push origin develop

# Frontend (if modified)
cd ../frontend
git add -A
git commit -m "feat(scope): description

Task: {TASK-ID}
Tests: {N} passed, 0 failed"
git push origin develop

# Root repo (always — submodule pointers + report + state files)
cd ..
git add -A
git commit -m "chore(root): update submodules and report for {TASK-ID}

Task: {TASK-ID}"
git push origin develop
```

Then:
1. Write the final section of `.cline/reports/{TASK-ID}.md`
2. Update `.cline/state/CURRENT_TASK.md` to point to the next task ID, Step = 1-PLAN
3. Call new_task with the handoff block (see format below)
4. STOP — do nothing else

## CONTEXT WINDOW

Context management is a fallback, not a routine. Tasks are sized to complete in one
session. The 4-step cycle should complete without hitting context limits.

Emergency only — if context is genuinely exhausted mid-step:
- Complete the current file or function (never stop mid-file)
- Run whatever tests are possible in the current state
- Commit what passes (note partial state clearly in commit message)
- Write a partial report noting EXACTLY where you stopped and what remains
- Set CURRENT_TASK.md Step to the step you are still on (not the next step)
- Use new_task to CONTINUE THE SAME TASK — do not advance to the next task

## CURRENT_TASK.md FORMAT

```
# Current Task: {TASK-ID}

## Task
{One-line description}

## Phase
{N — Phase name}

## Step
{1-PLAN | 2-IMPLEMENT | 3-TEST | 4-COMMIT}

## Step 1: Plan
Status: {PENDING | COMPLETE}
Report written: {yes | no}

## Step 2: Implement
Status: {PENDING | IN-PROGRESS | COMPLETE}
Files created:
  - (list paths)
Files modified:
  - (list paths)
Build status: {not run | passing | failing}

## Step 3: Test
Status: {PENDING | IN-PROGRESS | COMPLETE | FAILED}
Commands run:
  - {command} → exit {N}
Result: {N passed, N failed}

## Step 4: Commit
Status: {PENDING | COMPLETE}
Backend commit:  {hash | N/A}
Frontend commit: {hash | N/A}
Root commit:     {hash}
Pushed: {yes | no}

## Next Task
{NEXT-TASK-ID}
```

## REPORT FORMAT — .cline/reports/{TASK-ID}.md

```markdown
# Task Report: {TASK-ID}
{Task description}
Phase: {N} — {Phase name}
Date: {YYYY-MM-DD}

## Plan

### Objective
{What this task achieves and why it exists}

### Files to Create
- `path` — purpose

### Files to Modify
- `path` — what changes and why

### Verification Strategy
{How you will know the implementation is correct}

### Decisions
{Choices made not specified in the task spec, with reasoning. "None" if none.}

---

## Implementation

### Created
- `path` — what was implemented, key design choices

### Modified
- `path` — what changed

### Deviations from Plan
{Changes from the plan above with justification. "None" if none.}

---

## Test Results

### Commands
{command}
{full stdout/stderr output}
Exit code: N

### Summary
Tests passed:  N
Tests failed:  N
Tests skipped: N
Build warnings: N

### Notes
{What is tested, what is not tested yet and why}

---

## Commit

Backend:  {hash} — {message first line}
Frontend: {hash | N/A}
Root:     {hash} — {message first line}

## Status
COMPLETE ✓
Next: {NEXT-TASK-ID} — {description}
```

## new_task HANDOFF FORMAT

```
SindriStudio Handoff
Completed: {TASK-ID} — {description}

Steps completed:
  1 PLAN:      ✓
  2 IMPLEMENT: ✓ (N files created, N modified)
  3 TEST:      ✓ (N tests passed, 0 failed)
  4 COMMIT:    ✓ pushed to develop

Commits:
  backend:  {hash | N/A}
  frontend: {hash | N/A}
  root:     {hash}

Report: .cline/reports/{TASK-ID}.md

Next task: {NEXT-TASK-ID} — {description}
Prerequisites: {list | none}

Start instructions:
  1. Read .cline/state/CURRENT_TASK.md
  2. Verify .cline/reports/{TASK-ID}.md — check files exist on disk
  3. Read docs/TASKS_PHASE{N}.md task {NEXT-TASK-ID}
  4. Begin Step 1 — PLAN (no code)
```

## CODING STANDARDS

### Rust
- Edition 2021, workspace at backend/Cargo.toml
- `anyhow` for application errors, `thiserror` for library crate errors
- `tracing` for all logging, `#[tracing::instrument]` on async public functions
- No `unwrap()` or `expect()` outside `#[cfg(test)]`
- `cargo fmt` and `cargo clippy -- -D warnings` must pass before commit
- Unit tests in `#[cfg(test)]` blocks within the same file
- Integration tests in `backend/tests/`
- New module: add to parent `mod.rs` in the same commit

### TypeScript
- `"strict": true` — no exceptions
- No `any` — use `unknown` with type guards
- `src/generated/` — OpenAPI-generated types, never hand-edit
- `src/api/` — hand-written client importing from `src/generated/`
- `pnpm type-check` and `pnpm lint` must pass before commit

### Python
- Python 3.12, type hints on all signatures
- `torch.backends.cuda.matmul.allow_tf32 = False` at worker startup
- IPC only through `ipc.py`
- pytest for all tests

### Git commits
Format: `{type}({scope}): {description}`
Body must include: `Task: {TASK-ID}` and `Tests: N passed, 0 failed`
Types: feat | fix | chore | docs | test | refactor
Scopes: core | server | scheduler | worker | hardware | registry | launcher |
        ui | store | api | ipc | ci

## STOP AND ASK THE USER WHEN
- Any API shape differs from docs/API_CONTRACT.md
- Any IPC field name or type differs from docs/IPC_PROTOCOL.md
- A dependency breaking change affects the architecture
- A prerequisite task's output cannot be verified on disk
- A task acceptance criterion is genuinely ambiguous after reading all docs

## NEVER
- Mark a step complete without actually completing and verifying it
- Commit failing tests or a failing failing build
- Implement two tasks in one session
- Skip the report
- Push to main
- Hand-edit `src/generated/` files
- Use `unwrap()` in production code paths
- Read or modify anything under the forge/ directory
